# Godot 4.6 .gitignore
# Purpose: Exclude build artifacts while preserving essential project files

# ============================================================================
# GODOT BUILD ARTIFACTS (DO NOT COMMIT)
# ============================================================================

# .godot/ - Generated build cache and imported assets
# Why exclude: This directory can be 100MB-500MB and is regenerated from source files
# Contains: Compiled scripts, processed textures, physics cache, etc.
.godot/

# .mono/ - C# build artifacts (only relevant if using C# instead of GDScript)
# Why exclude: Compiled .NET assemblies, can be regenerated
.mono/

# data_*/ - Editor-specific temporary data
# Why exclude: Per-machine editor state, not part of project
data_*/

# ============================================================================
# EXPORT/BUILD OUTPUTS (DO NOT COMMIT)
# ============================================================================

# Executable builds (platform-specific)
*.exe           # Windows executable
*.pck           # Godot packed game data
*.app           # macOS application bundle
*.dmg           # macOS disk image
*.zip           # Compressed build archives
*.apk           # Android package
*.ipa           # iOS package

# Export presets - CAREFULLY CONSIDER
# Why you might exclude: Contains absolute paths to export templates (machine-specific)
# Why you might include: Team needs shared export settings
# Decision: Exclude by default, document export settings in README if needed
export_presets.cfg

# ============================================================================
# OPERATING SYSTEM FILES (DO NOT COMMIT)
# ============================================================================

# macOS
.DS_Store           # Finder metadata
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
._*

# Windows
Thumbs.db           # Image cache
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/

# Linux
.directory          # KDE folder settings
*~                  # Backup files

# ============================================================================
# IDE AND EDITOR FILES (DO NOT COMMIT)
# ============================================================================

# VSCode
.vscode/            # Settings, launch configs (machine-specific)

# JetBrains IDEs (Rider, IntelliJ)
.idea/
*.iml

# Vim/Neovim
*.swp
*.swo
*.swn
.vim/

# Emacs
*~
\#*\#
.\#*

# Sublime Text
*.sublime-workspace
*.sublime-project

# ============================================================================
# WHAT YOU *SHOULD* COMMIT
# ============================================================================
# ✅ .tscn files (scenes - defines node hierarchies)
# ✅ .gd files (scripts - game logic)
# ✅ .tres files (resources - data definitions)
# ✅ .import files (import settings for assets)
# ✅ project.godot (project configuration)
# ✅ All asset source files (.png, .jpg, .ogg, .wav, etc.)
# ✅ README.md, LICENSE, documentation
# ✅ addons/ folder (third-party plugins)
#
# CRITICAL: Do NOT add .tscn or .gd to .gitignore!
# These are your actual project files, not generated artifacts.

# ============================================================================
# PROJECT-SPECIFIC EXCLUSIONS (CUSTOMIZE AS NEEDED)
# ============================================================================

# Exclude large asset archives if you unpack them into assets/
# Example: If you download "sprout-lands-asset-pack.zip" and extract it
# sprout-lands-asset-pack.zip

# Exclude prototype/experimental folders
# prototype/
# experiments/

# Exclude private notes or design docs with sensitive info
# private_notes.md

# ============================================================================
# SAVE GAMES AND USER DATA (CONSIDER CAREFULLY)
# ============================================================================
# If your game saves to user:// (recommended), this is auto-handled
# If saving to project folder (NOT recommended), exclude save files:
# saves/
# *.save

# ============================================================================
# LOGS (DO NOT COMMIT)
# ============================================================================
logs/
*.log
